Japan, Thailand, India, China, Singapore: Asian Bond and Currency Preview

-- B y   S u r y a n i   O m a r
-- 
2011-07-25T22:21:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/japan-thailand-india-china-singapore-asian-bond-and-currency-preview.html
The following events and economic
reports may influence trading in  Asia ’s bonds and currencies
today. Bond yields and exchange rates are from the previous
trading session unless stated otherwise.  Japan: Chief Cabinet Secretary Yukio Edano, Finance
Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  and Economy Minister  Kaoru Yosano  will
hold media briefings after a Cabinet meeting.  The yield on the 1.2 percent government bond due June 2021
was 1.085 percent, according to Japan Bond Trading Co., the
nation’s largest interdealer debt broker.  The yen traded at 78.28 per dollar at 7:10 a.m. in Tokyo.  Thailand: The central bank will sell a combined 60 billion
baht ($2 billion) of bills today. It will also offer 25 billion
baht of securities due 2013.  The baht was at 29.74 per dollar.  India: The  Reserve Bank  of India will keep the cash reserve
ratio unchanged at 6 percent, according to the median forecast
of economists in a Bloomberg survey.  The yield on the 7.80 percent bond due April 2021 was 8.29
percent. The rupee was at 44.3875.  China: Agricultural Development Bank will offer 15 billion
yuan ($2.3 billion) of three-year notes.  The yield on the 3.99 percent bond due June 2021 was 4.08
percent, according to Chinabond, the nation’s biggest debt-
clearing house. The yuan was at 6.4450.  Singapore: Industrial production gained 8.8 percent in June
from a year ago after a 17.5 percent decline the previous month,
economists predicted in a Bloomberg survey ahead of data today.  The yield on the 2.25 percent bond due June 2021 was 2.11
percent. The  Singapore  dollar was at S$1.2073.  Philippines: The statistics office will report the nation’s
trade balance for May. The country had a deficit of $1.2 billion
in April.  The peso was at 42.405 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Suryani Omar in Jakarta at 
 somar6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Regan  at   jregan19@bloomberg.net . 